  <section class="ash-section ash-section--dark ash-faq">
    <div class="ash-wrap ash-section-head">
      <p class="ash-kicker">FAQ</p>
      <h2>Before you choose ASH</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="ash-wrap ash-faq__wrap">
      <div class="ash-faq__list">
        <details>
          <summary><span>What is the ASH driver configuration?</span></summary>
          <p>ASH uses one 13mm graphene diaphragm dynamic driver and six balanced armature drivers in a 4-way TrueXross hybrid system.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary><span>Why use a 13mm graphene dynamic driver?</span></summary>
          <p>The large graphene driver gives ASH its physical bass and lower-mid body. Its size, stiffness, and low mass help produce a powerful yet natural foundation.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary><span>Is ASH suitable for stage use?</span></summary>
          <p>Yes. ASH was designed for band performances, artists, worship events, and listeners who want a large, immersive hybrid signature. Final stage suitability depends on fit, isolation needs, and monitoring volume.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary><span>Should I choose universal or custom fit?</span></summary>
          <p>Choose universal fit for quicker auditioning and easier sharing. Choose custom fit for ear-impression shells, stronger passive isolation, and a more personal long-session fit.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

